    <briefdescription>
<para>Structure representing a single minute data record returned by <ref refid="group___health_service_1gad42347be400c448e5fceda786019611c" kindref="member">health_service_get_minute_history()</ref>. The <computeroutput>orientation</computeroutput> field encodes the angle of the watch in the x-y plane (the &quot;yaw&quot;) in the lower 4 bits (360 degrees linearly mapped to 1 of 16 different values) and the angle to the z axis (the &quot;pitch&quot;) in the upper 4 bits. The <computeroutput>vmc</computeroutput> value is a measure of the total amount of movement seen by the watch. More vigorous movement yields higher VMC values. </para>
    </briefdescription>
